#9f -> how does mpg chnage with other variables

plt.subplot(3,2,1)
sns.lineplot(x=auto["cylinders"],y=auto["mpg"])

plt.subplot(3,2,2)
sns.lineplot(x=auto["displacement"],y=auto["mpg"])

plt.subplot(3,2,3)
sns.lineplot(x=auto["horsepower"],y=auto["mpg"])

plt.subplot(3,2,4)
sns.lineplot(x=auto["weight"],y=auto["mpg"])

plt.subplot(3,2,5)
sns.lineplot(x=auto["acceleration"],y=auto["mpg"])

plt.subplot(3,2,6)
sns.lineplot(x=auto["year"],y=auto["mpg"])

plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()

#From the plots we can see that there is a strong co-relation between "mpg", "horsepower", "displacement" and "weight". 
#Thus if we wish to predict "mpg", we can use these three variables as predictors.
